Observability Basics – Locked Specification (MVP)

Scope

This document locks the minimum viable observability for the platform.

Constraints:
	•	No expensive tools (Datadog/Elastic)
	•	Must still support debugging real money/orders issues

Chosen approach:
	•	A) Lowest-cost, low-effort managed: Grafana Cloud free tier for logs/metrics (where possible)
	•	Java produces structured logs + metrics + audit logs in Postgres

⸻

1) Logging (Locked)

1.1 Structured JSON logs
	•	All services emit JSON logs to stdout
	•	Use Logback + JSON encoder

1.2 Correlation fields (required)

Every log line must include:
	•	traceId (request correlation ID)
	•	tenantId (nullable for public endpoints)
	•	userId (nullable for public endpoints)
	•	service (service/module name)
	•	env (dev/stage/prod)
	•	method, path, status, durationMs (for request logs)

1.3 MDC propagation
	•	Use SLF4J MDC to inject: traceId, tenantId, userId
	•	Ensure MDC is cleared at request end

1.4 Redaction (mandatory)

Never log:
	•	secrets (API keys)
	•	payment tokens
	•	full card data/CVV

PII guidance:
	•	Phone/email can be logged only when necessary for debugging
	•	Prefer masking in logs; keep full values in DB records if needed

⸻

2) Request IDs (Locked)

2.1 Trace ID generation
	•	On every incoming request:
	•	Read X-Trace-Id if provided
	•	Otherwise generate UUID v4
	•	Return X-Trace-Id on every response

2.2 Trace ID usage
	•	traceId must be included:
	•	in all logs
	•	in all error responses
	•	in audit events (detail JSON)

⸻

3) Audit Logs (Locked)

3.1 Audit logs live in Postgres

Audit events are stored in a dedicated DB table and retained long-term.

Required fields:
	•	tenant_id, user_id (nullable for system/webhook)
	•	action
	•	resource_type, resource_id
	•	detail (JSON)
	•	created_at

3.2 Sensitive actions to audit (locked list)
	•	PAYMENT_MARKED_PAID
	•	REFUND_EXECUTED
	•	ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED
	•	PAYMENT_SETTINGS_UPDATED
	•	STAFF_INVITED
	•	STAFF_ROLE_CHANGED
	•	STAFF_DISABLED
	•	SITE_PUBLISH (when publish is enabled)
	•	DOMAIN_CHANGED (when domain module is implemented)

Audit detail must include:
	•	traceId
	•	reason/note (when relevant)
	•	old/new values for status transitions

3.3 Retention
	•	Audit events retained ≥ 365 days (minimum)

⸻

4) Metrics (Locked)

4.1 Collection
	•	Java services expose Prometheus-format metrics (Micrometer)

4.2 Minimum metrics to track
	•	HTTP request count, latency, error rate
	•	Checkout/order creation failures
	•	Payment webhook processing success/failure
	•	Refund count

4.3 Storage & dashboards
	•	Use Grafana Cloud (free tier) for:
	•	dashboards
	•	alerts
	•	logs (Loki)
	•	metrics (Prometheus)

⸻

5) Rate Limiting (Locked)

5.1 Applies to public endpoints

Rate limit these endpoints:
	•	public checkout initiation
	•	public cart actions (if exposed)
	•	payment initiation endpoints

5.2 Enforcement points
	•	Primary: Cloudflare edge rate-limits
	•	Secondary: server-side token bucket (optional fallback)

5.3 Default thresholds
	•	Per IP: 10 checkout attempts / 1 minute
	•	Per tenant: 100 checkout attempts / 10 minutes

Response behavior:
	•	HTTP 429
	•	Include Retry-After
	•	Include traceId

⸻

6) Alerts (Locked)

6.1 Channels
	•	Slack + Email (MVP)

6.2 Minimum alert triggers
	•	Payment webhook failures > 5 in 5 minutes
	•	Checkout failure rate > 5% over 5 minutes
	•	HTTP 5xx rate > 1% over 5 minutes
	•	Latency p95 > 2s over 10 minutes

⸻

7) Retention & Cost Control (Locked)
	•	High-volume service logs retained 14 days in Grafana Cloud (or configured free-tier limits)
	•	Audit logs retained ≥ 365 days in Postgres
	•	Optional: archive logs to Cloudflare R2 for cheap long-term storage

⸻

8) Implementation Requirements (Locked)
	•	Add an HTTP filter/interceptor to set traceId + MDC + response header
	•	Configure Logback JSON encoder
	•	Add audit write helpers in services that perform sensitive actions
	•	Add Micrometer Prometheus registry
	•	Configure Cloudflare rate limiting rules for public checkout endpoints

⸻

9) Final Locked Summary
	•	Approach: Grafana Cloud free tier for logs/metrics/dashboards/alerts
	•	JSON structured logs with MDC correlation: traceId, tenantId, userId
	•	X-Trace-Id generated/returned on every request
	•	Postgres audit table for sensitive actions (≥ 1 year retention)
	•	Rate limiting at Cloudflare edge (default thresholds defined)
	•	Slack + Email alerts for payment/checkout failures

This specification is locked and implementation-ready.